# Project Structure Guide

The application boots from [main.js](mdc:main.js), which creates a canvas and hands it to the 3-D scene initializer in [MainScene.js](mdc:src/animations/MainScene.js).

Inside this scene file you will find the orchestration of

* vector rendering logic in [VectorVisualization.js](mdc:src/components/VectorVisualization.js)
* weight-matrix geometry in [WeightMatrixVisualization.js](mdc:src/components/WeightMatrixVisualization.js)
* supporting utility functions such as color mapping in [colors.js](mdc:src/utils/colors.js) and constants in [constants.js](mdc:src/utils/constants.js)

High-level animation helpers live in the `src/animations` directory, for example vector arithmetic animations are implemented in [VectorAdditionAnimation.js](mdc:src/animations/VectorAdditionAnimation.js) and [VectorMultiplicationAnimation.js](mdc:src/animations/VectorMultiplicationAnimation.js).

Use this map to quickly jump between the entry point, scene setup, and reusable visualization components.
